`crates/ctx-cage/src/` is the sandboxing crate that isolates an autonomous agent run's blast radius ‚Äî filesystem, namespaces, and network egress ‚Äî while leaving content-filtering/tool-brokering to `ctx-context`. Its two binaries (`bin/`) are thin front doors; everything else here is the machinery `lifecycle::execute()` orchestrates on their behalf.

The control flow for one caged run: `cli.rs` resolves argv into a validated `Mode`; `lifecycle/` runs prepare‚Üírun‚Üíteardown against a `Resolved` config (which itself pulls tool paths from `runtime.rs` for billed modes and mount args from `bwrap/`); `proxy.rs`/`proxy/` is the only egress path a running cage has, reached via a UNIX socket bound into the sandbox. `error.rs`'s `CageError` is the single error type threaded through all of it ‚Äî module-specific detail stays local, only genuinely cross-cutting failures get new variants there.

Two ADRs bind multiple files together and must be kept mutually consistent: ADR-046 (target_root is bound at its real host path, no fixed alias ‚Äî enforced in `bwrap/config.rs`, consumed by `runtime.rs`'s `synth_claude_config` project-map key, documented in `lib.rs`) and ADR-049 (offline stub `resolv.conf`, defined in `bwrap/` and asset-embedded via `lib.rs`'s `CAGE_RESOLV_CONF`). Billed-mode gating is the other cross-cutting seam: `cli.rs` requires `--allow-spend`, `lifecycle/prepare.rs` requires a clean git tree and resolves `ClaudeRuntime` via `runtime.rs`, `lifecycle/run.rs` starts the proxy only then, and `lifecycle/env.rs` adds `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` (never the raw API key) only then ‚Äî all four must agree on what counts as billed.

Invariant spanning the crate: the real API key never enters the cage process directly ‚Äî only `proxy.rs`, host-side, injects it (or passes through OAuth `Authorization` unmodified), per `ProxyConfig.api_key`. `lib.rs`'s embedded `CAGE_RULES_MD` and `CAGE_RESOLV_CONF` make it a compile failure to ship a binary missing either asset.